Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.93,0:00:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.56,0:00:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot Springs Park?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.23,0:00:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like fun to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.44,0:00:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's give it a try!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.57,0:00:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,100)\1c&HD2D3CE&\3c&H62452A&}Flowers dance to the piano's rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.54,0:00:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,0)\1c&HD2D3CE&\3c&H62452A&}Two people face-to-face is a mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.67,0:00:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,0)\1c&HD2D3CE&\3c&H62452A&}Find out the alibi trick based on\Nthe outdoor spa's blind spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:29.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\xshad0.1\fad(100,100)\1c&HD2D3CE&\3c&H62452A&}Perceiving to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.11,0:00:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,50)\xshad1.3\1c&H6AE8FA&\4c&H294A50&\}The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.08,0:00:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,50)\xshad1.3\1c&H6AE8FA&\4c&H294A50&\}His name is: Detective {\t(1670,1671,\1c&H4331B1&)}Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.24,0:02:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no use in stalling!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.23,0:02:29.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Why won't you just hurry up and sign this contract!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.70,0:02:29.03,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\be5\fad(210,0)}Umezu Hideaki (70)\N{\fs13}Mortgage Company President
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.33,0:02:32.63,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\be5\fad(250,0)}Maekawa Koichi (50)\N{\fs13}Hot Spring Park Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.33,0:02:32.63,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I told you many times that I have no desire to sell this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.16,0:02:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What an incapable successor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.91,0:02:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seriously think you can gather customers by selling octopuses here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.42,0:02:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because of a certain gargoyle perching over my\Nplace that the customers are being driven away!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.97,0:02:49.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.22,0:02:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be prepared to be disappointed by these lousy hot springs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.27,0:02:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.89,0:02:55.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.98,0:02:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, just ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.51,0:03:01.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This happens all the time, so don't mind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:05.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's right. Dad only comes here to pick fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.07,0:03:01.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ehara Mari (35)\NUmezu Hideaki's First Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.45,0:03:05.58,Signs,,0,0,0,,Umeze Yasuko (28)\NUmezu Hideaki's Second Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.78,0:03:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enough of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.99,0:03:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're all grown up, yet all you can do is mooch off of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have you know that you're to be quiet and respect my decisions!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.49,0:03:14.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oww!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.29,0:03:20.62,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The reason our president comes to this place is for business.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.92,0:03:20.62,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\be5\fad(210,0)}Yagihashi Shousuke (27)\N{\fs13}Umezu Hideaki's Secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.21,0:03:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.59,0:03:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's head inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.34,0:03:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You say we'll be disappointed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.10,0:03:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet you go in anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.63,0:03:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two adults and one child.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.42,0:03:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sincerely apologize for embarrassing you with our fight earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was that man with such a big attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.06,0:03:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the president from a mortgage company.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.51,0:03:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over the past month, he's been frequenting out private outdoor spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.35,0:03:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Business harassment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.61,0:03:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to prepare some freshly caught octopuses...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.25,0:03:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So please come to our restaurant after your baths.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.00,0:04:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.99,0:04:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right! Spa first and octopus later!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.13,0:04:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like we're starting to run low on octopuses...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.30,0:04:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'll go to the coast and catch some.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.09,0:04:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take care of the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.93,0:04:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? But low tide is at 8:02 today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.30,0:04:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One hour earlier won't make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.02,0:04:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.48,0:04:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such a variety of baths!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.77,0:04:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't decide!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.69,0:04:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's check out the iron tub first!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.28,0:04:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such a nice bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.87,0:04:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, the heat's starting to get to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Already?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.42,0:04:48.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is it all right for you to get in the spa even when you're injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.96,0:04:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's why I'll only take a light dip in the jacuzzi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't wring a towel while I'm like this, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.27,0:04:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.31,0:05:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This spa is fabulous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.19,0:05:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My body's floating on the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.19,0:05:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm heading out now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.48,0:05:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weird child.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.40,0:05:12.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't she...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.62,0:05:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.62,0:05:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drinking beer again...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to be driving later?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.38,0:05:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No need to worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've decided that we'll stay at a nearby hotel tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.47,0:05:36.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was actually your plan all along, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.93,0:05:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The octoputh'th thucktion cup'th getting on me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.77,0:05:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arm will still move even after it's cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it fresh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.90,0:05:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I used a harpoon to capture these during low tide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But other times, I use octopus pots or longlines to trap them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.11,0:05:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you figure out where to place the pots and longlines?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.28,0:05:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I float a buoy to mark the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:05:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do other people around here fish for octopuses too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.37,0:06:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just me, since I'm specially trained as a fisherman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.33,0:06:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I only do when I feel like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my dad suddenly died a year ago, so I've\Nbecome this place's manager on short notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.46,0:06:13.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.26,0:06:16.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was probably from the private outdoor spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.72,0:06:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go check out the private outdoor spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.56,0:06:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.29,0:06:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,President...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.04,0:06:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.62,0:06:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.25,0:06:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no use, he's already stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.13,0:06:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please call the police and an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.05,0:06:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.10,0:07:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased is mortgage company president, Umezu Hideaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.19,0:07:12.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He frequented this private outdoor spa every night, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.07,0:07:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.65,0:07:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found him bleeding from his head and sitting in the spa...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.66,0:07:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was at exactly 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.45,0:07:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A loud tumbling and splashing sound came from this outdoor spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.41,0:07:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rock on the cliff was close to tumbling off...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.33,0:07:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was about to schedule a maintenance appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.71,0:07:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Safety management is a grave responsibility, you know!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:34.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.76,0:07:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.51,0:07:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rock fell from that cliff and hit Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s head.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.93,0:07:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, retrieve that rock immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.56,0:07:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.18,0:07:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, let me help too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.85,0:07:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't require your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.77,0:07:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.65,0:07:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This rock is covered in quite a bit of moss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.24,0:08:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bloodstains and hair are attached on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.00,0:08:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the rock broke off and fell from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, there are friction marks on the nearby rocks around that hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.84,0:08:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.01,0:08:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.63,0:08:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me someone tried to force the rock out...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:26.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And caused the scratch marks by wiggling the rock around!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.77,0:08:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the rock didn't naturally\Nfall off the cliff and hit Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.73,0:08:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather, someone stood on top of the cliff\Nand threw the rock directly at Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.48,0:08:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is not an accident, but a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.11,0:08:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we did hear sounds resembling a rock rolling down the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.07,0:08:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the rock was heavy, they rolled it over the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.33,0:08:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At this height, it was impossible for\Nanyone to enter from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:09:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the only passage to get here is from that glass door.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.63,0:09:05.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A crime committed by someone from this\Nhot springs park at 8:00, so it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.22,0:09:09.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, everyone gather in the lobby!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.23,0:09:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'll bring some tea here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:16.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.74,0:09:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you! Where were you looking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.49,0:09:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.62,0:09:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.71,0:09:36.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there's no need for tea, so please come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.17,0:09:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.55,0:09:41.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want to talk to us about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.67,0:09:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was apparently murdered by someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.47,0:09:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the estimated time of death around 8:00 PM, the relevant\Nparties in the spas of this hot springs park were you three people!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.27,0:09:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would like to ask what you were doing\Nand your whereabouts during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.65,0:10:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.11,0:10:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that you're suspecting us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.78,0:10:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, I'll question the person who met with Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nlast - his secretary Yagihashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, if you please!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.66,0:10:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around 7:00, I was helping the president get changed in the locker room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.75,0:10:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After I sent the president off, I received a call from work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the time I went in the spa, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had\Nalready been in there for five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.67,0:10:25.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you at around 8:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.93,0:10:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was taking a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.01,0:10:30.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that I heard the commotion...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.10,0:10:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's only a short distance from the showers to the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.15,0:10:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.23,0:10:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the eldest daughter, Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I entered the spa some time after the detective's daughter did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And once there, I was in the jacuzzi the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.99,0:10:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, you can smell the jasmine from my hair, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.95,0:10:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jasmine?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to enhance the healing effects of\Nour jacuzzi, we supplement it with herbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.54,0:10:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.67,0:11:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.79,0:11:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went in the spa earlier than both Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Yasuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.84,0:11:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The jacuzzi is right next to the private outdoor spa, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.30,0:11:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had an opportunity to commit the crime as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.47,0:11:14.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop blurting out nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.48,0:11:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the younger daughter, Yasuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.27,0:11:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was talking to a friend on the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.36,0:11:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I got in the spa about five minutes later than my sister did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.36,0:11:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at the reclining spa in the far back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.99,0:11:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But sometime before 8:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw Yasuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} headed for the mist sauna.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.49,0:11:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yagihashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:40.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh my, what were you two doing in the mist?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.96,0:11:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We... happened to bump into each other at the sauna, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, Officer, you forgot about the most suspicious party.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.88,0:11:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our president was about to buyout this hot springs park.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.01,0:11:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't the manager, Maekawa, have held a grudge over this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.35,0:11:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The female staff member was confirmed to be\Nat the front desk by the security camera...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.35,0:12:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you were not present at all times!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.52,0:12:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since we were running low on octopuses,\NI went out to catch some at sea around 7:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.57,0:12:12.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From 7:30 to 8:00 I was in the restaurant,\Nand Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} can attest to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.95,0:12:14.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.33,0:12:18.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was with me in the restaurant the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.54,0:12:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To recap, of the four people relating to Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, all of\Nyou except Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were in the hot springs park...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.05,0:12:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And had the opportunity to murder him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.76,0:12:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The elder daughter, Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was at the jacuzzi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.05,0:12:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The younger daughter, Yasuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was at the reclining spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.22,0:12:38.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the secretary, Yagihashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was in the showers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.81,0:12:41.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two have motives, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.27,0:12:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father was fiercely opposed to the two of them getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.48,0:12:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're trying to incriminate us, you'd also be one to benefit from this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.07,0:12:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.49,0:12:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, your business did poorly and you're in debt now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.28,0:12:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to pay them off, you would want to sink\Nyour claws into dad's assets, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.04,0:13:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't just go saying whatever you please!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.37,0:13:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, is it true that you merely "happened"\Nto bump into Yasuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at the sauna?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.46,0:13:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.72,0:13:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.26,0:13:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured since dad opposed our marriage,\Nwe could run away or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had planned to do just that after the buyout of this park was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.60,0:13:25.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're just spitting a bunch of rubbish out of your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.73,0:13:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer, don't be fooled by this man's words!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.44,0:13:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of his attempt to marry Yasuko,\Nfather angrily told him to learn his place!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.74,0:13:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he held a grudge...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.41,0:13:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You ungrateful goon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.96,0:13:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.67,0:13:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.96,0:13:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, did you figure out who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.84,0:13:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.93,0:13:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet that the culprit didn't want to leave their fingerprints behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they used a towel to wrap around the\Nrock before throwing it at Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.64,0:14:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the towel should have moss on it that came off of the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.32,0:14:12.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see green smudges here, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.49,0:14:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that this towel...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.11,0:14:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.78,0:14:19.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was something like that inside my bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.58,0:14:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it won't do you any good to\Ntry and talk your way out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.83,0:14:25.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll find out for ourselves after having this towel examined.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:27.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.58,0:14:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll explain everything in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.80,0:14:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, come to the private outdoor spa!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.21,0:14:34.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.47,0:14:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not good, at this rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.35,0:14:41.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, what's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.48,0:14:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just wondering why I was able to stay\Non top of the water in that float spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.98,0:14:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.19,0:14:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the Dead Sea, it contains a high\Nconcentration of salt which makes you float.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.20,0:14:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Float...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.41,0:14:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.32,0:15:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.96,0:15:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.26,0:15:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.67,0:15:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I've figured out the trick that the culprit used.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.02,0:15:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.06,0:15:32.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're always running off at the drop of a hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.52,0:15:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.28,0:15:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, Uncle Kogorou asked me to do something...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.57,0:15:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, let's get things started!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.00,0:15:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason I named Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as the culprit was...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.38,0:15:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just for laughs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.71,0:15:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.17,0:15:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now is not the time for laughs...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.09,0:16:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, quiet down and listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.22,0:16:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your right hand is injured, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.02,0:16:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.10,0:16:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a wound like that, it would be difficult to tightly wring a towel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.61,0:16:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wring a towel...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.11,0:16:19.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that towel was tightly wrung!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.45,0:16:20.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.36,0:16:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, that towel did not belong to Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.66,0:16:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the towel did come out of her bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.62,0:16:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit put it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.83,0:16:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to place the blame on Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:34.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.21,0:16:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, that ended up exposing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They didn't think deep enough about Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.89,0:16:43.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, how did the culprit do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s been carrying her bag all along,\Nso the only chance to put it there...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.69,0:16:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.69,0:16:55.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.73,0:16:58.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.24,0:17:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the crime, Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has an alibi of being with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.36,0:17:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingernails were ragged and dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.95,0:17:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's plausible that Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't die after being hit by the rock...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.04,0:17:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But from having his head forced under the water and being drowned!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.50,0:17:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingernails were ragged and dirty was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.63,0:17:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he was struggling and scratching at the bottom of the spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.43,0:17:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Verify this with forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.85,0:17:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.14,0:17:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, we rushed here soon after we\Nheard the noise made by the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.19,0:17:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to drown a person in such a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.90,0:17:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when was Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drowned?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.40,0:17:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the disposable shampoo and soap.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.69,0:17:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of them were used.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.61,0:17:44.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The seats weren't used either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.49,0:17:48.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right! They weren't used at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed as soon as he entered the spa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.71,0:17:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around 7:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.08,0:18:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Yagihashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Yasuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and\NMari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were still in the locker room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.63,0:18:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only person capable of committing the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:05.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.35,0:18:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, you went to catch octopuses despite\Nthe fact that it was an hour too early for low tide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.56,0:18:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You actually didn't go to catch octopuses, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.69,0:18:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You quickly hid yourself near the private spa...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.94,0:18:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And without him suspecting anything,\Nyou brained Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.70,0:18:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you forced his head under the water and drowned him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:30.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.24,0:18:34.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard the noise at 8:00 as well, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.92,0:18:41.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the time of the crime was 7:00,\Nthen who rolled the rock at 8:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.26,0:18:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was in the restaurant at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.89,0:18:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan, do what I just taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.93,0:18:51.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.14,0:18:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.97,0:18:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo, carry that rock and climb up this cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.74,0:18:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.32,0:19:03.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This rock sure is heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.49,0:19:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see a small harbor down there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.95,0:19:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.45,0:19:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.21,0:19:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This rope was tied to the buoy near the harbor\Nâ€” it's a type of rope called a longline.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.50,0:19:22.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Longline?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grab the longline and pull it straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.55,0:19:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, tilt the rock you just brought up forward at the edge of the cliff...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.31,0:19:33.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then use the wooden rod to support the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.48,0:19:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this, we're all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.81,0:19:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.69,0:19:43.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:52.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:20:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sea entered low tide at 8:00 and had the lowest water level.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.21,0:20:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, the buoy floating in the sea went down as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.13,0:20:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The buoy pulled the line down, which removed\Nthe rod and caused the rock to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:12.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, he used low tide as his time difference trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Low tide...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.47,0:20:20.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The would-be evidences of the rope and the rod then\Nflew off the ledge, headed straight to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.27,0:20:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.98,0:20:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're able to see that part of the ledge has been chipped away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.15,0:20:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.69,0:20:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those friction marks were made by the hooks attached to the longline.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.37,0:20:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was pretty telltale.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.74,0:20:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, using this method...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.79,0:20:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could cause the rock to roll down at 8:00,\Neven if he were in a different place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.38,0:20:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an interesting deduction, but that's\Nall circumstantial evidence, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.55,0:20:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any concrete evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.38,0:20:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maekawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, why have you kept your pants rolled up all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.18,0:20:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you roll them down?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.56,0:20:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.68,0:20:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.56,0:21:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you brained Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with the rock,\Nhis blood splattered on your pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.11,0:21:06.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You only noticed that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.86,0:21:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you saw forensics roll up his pants to retrieve the rock from the spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.24,0:21:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then unconsciously glanced at your pants...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.87,0:21:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And hurriedly rolled them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.46,0:21:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police had already started their investigation, so\Nyou couldn't change them without raising suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.22,0:21:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We now have the decisive evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.38,0:21:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, you held a grudge against our president\Nbecause he tried to buyout your hot springs park!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.77,0:21:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.93,0:21:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A year ago, my father was driven to despair by his debts to Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.15,0:21:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he got drunk, and ended up drowning in the spa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.73,0:21:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I followed my father's will and used his life\Ninsurance to reconstruct this hot springs park...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.61,0:21:53.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tried to make it big, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.74,0:21:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But after all, I'm a man of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.37,0:21:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't support myself on the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.00,0:22:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, I couldn't fight against Umezu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s buyout...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.71,0:22:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured if he were going to rob me of this place, then\NI'd just bury him with the entire hot springs park.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.26,0:22:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I carried out my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.68,0:23:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His snoring is so loud I can't sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.56,0:23:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I can't sleep at all!
